THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
----------------------
Shimmer depends on the following open-source projects, each of which
retains its own license:

  NumPy            BSD-3-Clause     https://numpy.org/
  SciPy            BSD-3-Clause     https://scipy.org/
  soundfile        BSD-3-Clause     https://github.com/bastibe/python-soundfile
  matplotlib       PSF-based        https://matplotlib.org/
  FastAPI          MIT              https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/
  uvicorn          BSD-3-Clause     https://www.uvicorn.org/
  python-multipart Apache-2.0       https://github.com/Kludex/python-multipart
  pyloudnorm       MIT              https://github.com/csteinmetz1/pyloudnorm

Optional, used by the Remix (stem separation) feature:

  Demucs           MIT              https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs

Demucs is installed on demand into an isolated virtual environment and is
invoked as a separate process. It is neither bundled with nor linked into
Shimmer.

Optional, used for MP3 / M4A / AAC support:

  ffmpeg           LGPL/GPL         https://ffmpeg.org/

ffmpeg is not distributed with Shimmer; it is located on the user's PATH
at runtime if present.
